{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "wood", "icon": "VOP/wood", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Wood"], "extent": [59, 68]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simulates shiny wood grain."], "extent": [68, 104]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator simulates shiny wood grain."], "extent": [104, 147]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Vein Frequency (", {"type": "code", "text": ["vfreq"]}, ") input controls the number of veins in the\npattern. For veins that fade out gradually, vary the Vein Attenuation\n(", {"type": "code", "text": ["vatten"]}, ") input."], "extent": [147, 307]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Vein Scale (", {"type": "code", "text": ["vscale"]}, ") input offers a good means of controlling the\nellipse ratio of the veins. Thus, tree stumps, which have rings of a\nfairly circular nature, should use a ", {"type": "code", "text": ["vscale"]}, " value close to one.\nLongitudinal cross-sections, on the other hand, are very elliptical and\nshould use a ", {"type": "code", "text": ["vscale"]}, " value greater or less than one."], "extent": [307, 640]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Groove Depth (", {"type": "code", "text": ["gdepth"]}, ") input allows you to displace the surface along\nthe vein area. A groove depth of zero will not generate any\ndisplacements at all. Alternatively, you can use the Vein Amount output\nin a separate displacement shader."], "extent": [640, 883]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator uses the Ripples pattern as the vein generator. Other\ntechniques include using the Veins operator with a cylindrical\nprojection and one-sided vein softness."], "extent": [883, 1055]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, "), Normal (", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, ") and texture coordinate (s t) inputs are\nnot connected, the global variables by the same names will be used\ninstead. Typically, you will use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as\ninputs for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ", and Shading Layer Parameter as the input for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["s"]}, " and\n", {"type": "code", "text": ["t"]}, ". You will not touch ", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, " unless you want to apply additional\ndisplacement to the wood surface using an operator such as ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpmap", "type": "link", "text": ["Bump Map"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpmap"}, ". If you need to access the global variables directly, they are\navailable from the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."], "extent": [1055, 1656]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1656, 1665], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}], "extent": [1665, 1689]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/marble", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/marble"}], "extent": [1689, 1709]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/ripples", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/ripples"}], "extent": [1709, 1730]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/shadinglayer", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/shadinglayer"}], "extent": [1730, 1756]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/veins", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/veins"}], "extent": [1756, 1775]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/woodplank", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/woodplank"}], "extent": [1775, 1799]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Wood"], "summary": ["Simulates shiny wood grain."]}